ity as vibrant as any in Europe.Petrovsky-Shtern brings this golden age to life, looking at dozens of shtetls and drawing on a wealth of never-before-used archival material. Illustrated throughout with rare archival photographs and artwork, this nuanced history casts the shtetl in an altogether new light, revealing how its golden age continues to shape the collective memory of the Jewish people today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aHistoryxJewish. 0aHistory. 0aJewsxSocial life and customs. 0aJewszEurope, EasternxSocial life and customs. 0aShtetlszEurope, EasternxHistory. 0aVillageszEurope, EasternxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311066592540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400851164zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400851164423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400851164.jpg  a978-3-11-066592-5  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK